trans-unit.source: Get Service Document
trans-unit.target: Get Service Document

trans-unit.source: The <languageKeyword>Get Service Document</languageKeyword> operation retrieves the service document, which describes the resources exposed by the Windows Azure Import/Export Service.
trans-unit.target: The <languageKeyword>Get Service Document</languageKeyword> operation retrieves the service document, which describes the resources exposed by the Windows Azure Import/Export Service.

trans-unit.source: The service document is defined by the Atom Publishing Protocol; for details, refer to <externalLink><linkText>RFC 5023</linkText><linkUri>http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5023</linkUri></externalLink>.
trans-unit.target: The service document is defined by the Atom Publishing Protocol; for details, refer to <externalLink><linkText>RFC 5023</linkText><linkUri>http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5023</linkUri></externalLink>.

trans-unit.source: In general you should not need to call this operation, as you will already have specified the resources you require in each REST request.
trans-unit.target: In general you should not need to call this operation, as you will already have specified the resources you require in each REST request.

trans-unit.source: If you are building a tool that relies on automatic discovery of resource updates, this operation may be useful to you.
trans-unit.target: If you are building a tool that relies on automatic discovery of resource updates, this operation may be useful to you.
